(436, 3, 49, 'grovel', 'grovel@gmx.net', 'Fill your website URL in if you have any :)', '84.226.165.47', '2010-02-25 17:03:26', '2010-02-25 17:03:26', 'Well, deviantArt''s rss-feed gives you three media entries per item: two thumbnails (with a 150px, and 300px dimension respectively) - I think you display the second of these (what I call the large thumbnail), arent''s you? Yet the feed also offers a media:content entry with the original size image.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nObviously you cannot access messages, set favs, and the like - but this can easily be remedied by the inclusion of a browser window (glad you''ll include this).<br />\r\nOn the other hand, the RSS-feeds are great and offer plenty of options.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor example, if you enter "boost%3Apopular+in%3Aphotography+max_age%3A24h" as the rss query, then you get the most popular items of the last 24 hours in the photography subsection. This can be queried for any of the categories (which you would have to set statically in your app - I suppose) and for a series of predefined timeframes.<br />\r\nAt the moment I use cooliris and pass these strings as search terms, but it is terribly slow - so a better app would be wonderful. Especially because the dev-art webapp sucks.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCheers and thumbsup,<br />\r\n<br />\r\ngrovel', 0, 0, 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 6.1; en; rv:1.9.2) Gecko/20100115 Firefox/3.6 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', 0, 0),
